ANTHRAX - UKRAINE: (CHERKASY) HUMAN, PORCINE
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 4 May 2012
Source: Novostey.com, MIGNews report [in Russian, trans. & summ., edited]
http://novostey.com/society/news402845.html

[A similar article (also in Russian) was published in SVIT 24 at http://svit24.net/events/42-events/22479-v-cherkasskoj-oblasty-zafyksyrovan-sluchaj-zarazhenyja-sybyrskoj-jazvoj]


In Cherkassy province a 38-year-old man developed anthrax from butchering pig carcasses. This was reported by the press service of the State Ministry of Emergencies in Cherkassy region. [Spelling of Cherkasy/Cherkassy/Cherkassi varies. - Mod.MHJ]

The incident occurred in the city of Zvenigorodka-Razdelnaya. The pork butcher had a cutaneous arm lesion and went to the district hospital where he was diagnosed with "anthrax". Doctors have collected materials for research in the laboratory of particularly dangerous infections. During the subsequent tests _Bacillus anthracis_ was cultured, the cause of anthrax, according to Glavred.

The patient was hospitalized in the infectious disease clinic and his condition is satisfactory. Meanwhile, experts from the public health centers and Veterinary Service are investigating to determine the source of transmission.

